GOLDBACH VERIFICATION ENGINE v2.0
=================================

Verifies Goldbach's Conjecture using dual-verified exact integer arithmetic.
Same credibility standard as y-cruncher (dual computation, SHA-256 hashing).

QUICK START
-----------

  ./build.sh        Build (auto-detects compiler + CPU)
  ./goldbach        Interactive menu
  ./goldbach 1e9    Verify up to 1 billion

Or one-liner on any Linux/macOS machine:

  bash build.sh && ./goldbach

REQUIREMENTS
------------

  - Any C compiler (gcc, clang, cc)
  - pthreads (included on Linux/macOS)
  - That's it. No libraries. No package managers.

CLUSTER USE
-----------

Split ranges across machines:

  Machine 1:  ./goldbach --range 4        1e15
  Machine 2:  ./goldbach --range 1e15     2e15
  Machine 3:  ./goldbach --range 2e15     3e15
  ...

Each machine outputs a SHA-256 hash. Combine to verify completeness.

FILES
-----

  goldbach.c          The entire engine (1100 lines, zero dependencies)
  build.sh            Build script (auto-detects compiler + CPU flags)
  README              This file

  Python prototypes (optional, for research/exploration):
  goldbach_fft.py     NTT convolution approach
  verify_shortcut.py  Shortcut scaling analysis
  goldbach_engine.py  Python segmented sieve verifier
  goldbach_beyond.py  Python beyond-record tester

